Package lab5

Class Container

java.lang.Object
lab5.Container
Direct Known Subclasses:
MyList, MySet
class Container extends Object
This class represents a container that stores objects in an array-like structure. Your implementation of this class or methods should not contains: 1. No System.out.println statements should appear here. Instead, you need to return the result. 2. No Scanner operations should appear here (e.g., input.nextInt()). Instead, refer to the input parameters of this method.

  • Method Details

    • add

      public void add(Object obj)
      Add the object obj to the end of the container. No check for duplication is required. If the list is full, the list's capacity is doubled, and the object is added to the end of list.
      Parameters:
      obj - is the object that is added to the container.

    • remove

      public Object remove(Object obj)
      This method removes the object from the container. It shifts all the elements to ensure that the element's removal does not create an empty location in the container. The method removes the first occurrence of the object. If the Object not found, return null
      Parameters:
      obj - is the object that is removed from the container.
      Returns:
      It returns the object that was removed.
